fields.Title: WHIRLING F2 / KLAASJE DOOR
fields.OverrideDialogueCondition: (Variable["whirling.klaasjedoor_opened"] == true)  or  Variable["TASK.arrest_klaasje_done"] == true  or  Variable["whirling.klaasje_arrest_decision_made_did_not_arrest"] == true  or  Variable["TASK.report_to_the_tribunal_done"] == true  or  Variable["whirling.barreddoor_opened_from_the_inside"] == true
fields.Description: When the dialogue with Klaasje is over you can go and click and her door.

fields.Title: Half Light: "You should punch a fucking hole in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You should punch a fucking hole in it.

fields.Title: Half Light: "The murmur in your ears recedes slo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The murmur in your ears recedes slowly, your breathing normalizes. That's one lucky door.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You swallow, like you swallowed the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You swallow, like you swallowed the last time. Whatever bitter emotion was swimming to the surface then -- and now -- subsides. Submerges. Sinks back into you.

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "Sounds like it's coming from upstai..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sounds like it's coming from upstairs somewhere -- you could snoop around before going up...

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "The door is closed."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door is closed.

fields.Title: You: "Knock again."
fields.Dialogue Text: Knock again.

fields.Title: You: "Knock."
fields.Dialogue Text: Knock.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We should come back in the morning.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "We should come back in the morning."

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "There is no answer."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is no answer.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Door, Room #3: "The door is closed."]
You: "Fucking whore."
fields.Dialogue Text: Fucking whore.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "White Mourning. It was mourning all..."
fields.Dialogue Text: White Mourning. It was mourning all along. You should've seen it coming, it was right behind her eyes...

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Caustic Echo. It was darkness all a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Caustic Echo. It was darkness all along. But you were young and it was summer. You just had to take a dive...

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "Still nothing."
fields.Dialogue Text: Still nothing.

fields.Title: You: "Knock again, much harder."
fields.Dialogue Text: Knock again, much harder.

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "This door can only be opened with a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This door can only be opened with a key or from the inside.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "A tremendous loneliness comes over..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A tremendous loneliness comes over you. Everybody in the world is doing something without you.

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "The door is closed."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door is closed.

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: ""Who is it?" A woman's voice answer..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Who is it?" A woman's voice answers -- muffled by the door.

fields.Title: You: "Try the handle."
fields.Dialogue Text: Try the handle.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Hey! What is your problem?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hey! What is your problem?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""This is the police. Can we come in?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "This is the police. Can we come in?"

fields.Title: Half Light: "You hear the murmur of blood in you..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You hear the murmur of blood in your ears. Your back slowly relaxes when you breathe out. That's one lucky door.

fields.Title: Shivers: "In the Jamrock Quarter, The Paliseu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In the Jamrock Quarter, The Paliseum for music, company and men... or the Door To The River, for death and synthetic opiates. Or, way in the East in Couron, in a starlit *boîte de nuits* like *La Cherte*... far from here and you, shivering dog.

fields.Title: Drama: "Tired. Controlled."
fields.Dialogue Text: Tired. Controlled.

fields.Title: You: ""Fucking whore!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Fucking whore!"

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "The door is indifferent to your lon..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door is indifferent to your loneliness. The world does not care.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You're just as alone as the last ti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You're just as alone as the last time. Whatever kept you company in this world -- what kept you safe -- has left your side, never to return again.

fields.Title: You: "Knock..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Knock...

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: ""Come on up -- the door is open!" S..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Come on up -- the door is open!" She shouts: "I'm drying my hair..."

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "You slam your fist into the vinyl...."
fields.Dialogue Text: You slam your fist into the vinyl. It does not produce a hole. The door sits sturdily in the frame and your fist hurts. This was all a very good, normal thing to do.

fields.Title: You: ""Beauty, don't abandon me in all th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Beauty, don't abandon me in all this ugliness!"

fields.Title: Empathy: "He doesn't like where this is going..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He doesn't like where this is going.

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "The door feels cold."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door feels cold.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: ""Why are you doing this? Don't do t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why are you doing this? Don't do this to me, please!" Remember? Who *was* that meant for?

fields.Title: You: "Knock."
fields.Dialogue Text: Knock.

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "The door does not care."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door does not care.

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "The door is closed."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door is closed.

fields.Title: Perception (Hearing): "You hear the shower being turned on..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You hear the shower being turned on, somewhere inside.

fields.Title: You: ""Why are you doing this? Don't do t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why are you doing this? Don't do this to me..."

fields.Title: Volition: "Don't. Everyone is a whore? What do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't. Everyone is a whore? What does that even mean? Breathe in and walk away.

fields.Title: You: ""I'm so alone.""
fields.Dialogue Text: "I'm so alone."

fields.Title: Half Light: "That felt good. Everyone is a whore..."
fields.Dialogue Text: That felt good. Everyone is a whore. Now punch a hole in the door.

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "The words still echo in the hallway..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The words still echo in the hallway...

fields.Title: Half Light: "There we go-- *fucking whore*. What..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There we go-- *fucking whore*. What a nice thing to say, Harry. Everything is A-Okay with you.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Somewhere not far from here the lie..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Somewhere not far from here the lieutenant is preparing her file. "Klaasje Amandou," he writes. You realize the detective should be here for what comes next. It could prove... *dangerous* to go in alone.

fields.Title: You: "Swallow the emotion."
fields.Dialogue Text: Swallow the emotion.

fields.Title: You: "Suppress the urge."
fields.Dialogue Text: Suppress the urge.

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "The door is mute and indifferent. Y..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door is mute and indifferent. Your despair is a joke to it.

fields.Title: You: "Run your finger across the dent."
fields.Dialogue Text: Run your finger across the dent.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "Beauty has abandoned you in this ug..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Beauty has abandoned you in this ugliness, honcho. And then some! You cannot even remember the *name* of beauty; what beauty was...

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "There is no answer -- it's nighttim..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There is no answer -- it's nighttime, officer.

fields.Title: Horrific Necktie: "The door probably thinks you're a h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The door probably thinks you're a has-been loser too. You feel your funny necktie becoming tighter and tighter around your neck...

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "This little depression is all you c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This little depression is all you could inflict on the door.

fields.Title: Door, Room #3: "Still no answer."
fields.Dialogue Text: Still no answer.

fields.Title: You: "Punch the door."
fields.Dialogue Text: Punch the door.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant gives you a quick gl..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant gives you a quick glance.

fields.Title: You: "Breathe in."
fields.Dialogue Text: Breathe in.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "There's still a dent in the vinyl -..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's still a dent in the vinyl -- where you punched it before.

fields.Title: You: "Knock..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Knock...

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "A young woman like this is probably..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A young woman like this is probably out partying the night away. Drink and drugs, sweet drugs are involved. Loneliness begone...

fields.Title: Electrochemistry: "As you hold the metal you sense the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As you hold the metal you sense the warmth left there by her hand.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "Not to mention *great* exercise!"
fields.Dialogue Text: Not to mention *great* exercise!

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Stop that!" The lieutenant sounds..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Stop that!" The lieutenant sounds angry.

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: "Just knock again."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just knock again.
